      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(queue): persist followup queues across gateway restarts",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the gateway process restarts (npm update, crash, systemd restart), any\nmessages that arrived while an agent turn was in progress are silently lost.\nThe followup queue lives only in process memory — there is no recovery path.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd persistence for the `FOLLOWUP_QUEUES` global map in shared SQLite state\n(`state/openclaw.sqlite`), matching AGENTS.md runtime queue policy.\n\n### Core: `src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.ts`\n\n- `persistFollowupQueues()` — serializes all non-empty queue entries into\n  `followup_queue_entries` on `openclaw.sqlite`. Respects `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`\n  via the existing `resolveStateDir()` utility. Rows are deleted when all\n  queues drain to empty.\n- `restoreFollowupQueues()` — reads persisted rows at module init and\n  repopulates `FOLLOWUP_QUEUES` before any enqueue or drain fires.\n- Persisted routing selectors include `originatingReplyToId` and\n  `inputProvenance` so restored runs keep reply-target context.\n\n### SQLite layer: `src/infra/followup-queue-sqlite.ts`\n\n- `replaceFollowupQueueEntries`, `loadFollowupQueueEntries`, and helpers used\n  by persist/restore and doctor migration.\n\n### Doctor migration: `src/infra/state-migrations.ts`\n\n- Migrates legacy `live-chat-followup-queues.json` sidecars into shared SQLite\n  and removes the JSON file when import succeeds (conflict-safe when SQLite\n  already has different data for the same queue key).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Queued followup messages survive gateway restart\n  and redeliver exactly once. Head `3a5baafd3` uses shared SQLite storage plus\n  doctor migration for legacy JSON sidecars.\n- Real environment tested: Local Linux checkout, Node 24, real temp state dir via\n  `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, real `openclaw.sqlite` and legacy JSON file I/O (no\n  in-memory mocks for persist/restore/migration).\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  ```bash\n  cd openclaw\n  pnpm exec vitest run \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue.followup-restart-roundtrip.test.ts \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/state-migrations.test.ts \\\n    src/infra/followup-queue-sqlite.test.ts\n  ```\n- Evidence after fix:\n  ```\n  Test Files  4 passed (4)\n       Tests  30 passed (30)\n\n  Covered behaviors on head 3a5baafd3:\n  - Telegram-routed followup → shared SQLite → simulated restart → exactly-once redelivery → no replay after second restart\n  - originatingReplyToId + inputProvenance round-trip\n  - Fresh install: followup_queue_entries table created on first openclaw.sqlite open\n  - Doctor: legacy live-chat-followup-queues.json → SQLite import, sidecar removed, restore repopulates queue\n  - Doctor conflict: stale JSON left in place when SQLite already has different data for the same key\n  - Secret-bearing config stripped; auth/reply selectors preserved\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: Restored items retain prompt, routing, reply target,\n  and provenance; drain delivers once; post-drain persistence prevents replay.\n- What was not tested: Live native Telegram desktop capture (prior Mantis run\n  failed on shared QA infra). Can be requested via `@openclaw-mantis` on this PR.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "feat/queue-followup-persistence",
